Here are both approaches for Shell navigation in .NET MAUI:

**1. Passing the product ID (string):**

```csharp
// ProductListPage.xaml.cs or ViewModel
async void OnProductTapped(Product product)
{
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"{nameof(ProductDetailsPage)}?productId={product.Id}");
}
```

**2. Passing the full object (via dictionary):**

```csharp
async void OnProductTapped(Product product)
{
    var navParams = new Dictionary<string, object>
    {
        { "product", product }
    };
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync(nameof(ProductDetailsPage), navParams);
}
```

**Receiving with `IQueryAttributable` on the ViewModel:**

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId { get => _productId; set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value); }
    public Product Product { get => _product; set => SetProperty(ref _product, value); }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach 1: simple string parameter
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from service if needed
        }

        // Approach 2: full object
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product product)
        {
            Product = product;
            ProductId = product.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

**Wire up the ViewModel as BindingContext:**

```csharp
// ProductDetailsPage.xaml.cs
public ProductDetailsPage(ProductDetailsViewModel vm)
{
    InitializeComponent();
    BindingContext = vm;
}
```

**Register routes and DI:**

```csharp
// MauiProgram.cs or AppShell
Routing.RegisterRoute(nameof(ProductDetailsPage), typeof(ProductDetailsPage));

// DI registration
builder.Services.AddTransient<ProductDetailsPage>();
builder.Services.AddTransient<ProductDetailsViewModel>();
```

**Key differences:**

| | String param | Object param |
|---|---|---|
| Syntax | Query string `?key=val` | `Dictionary<string, object>` overload |
| In `ApplyQueryAttributes` | Value arrives as `string` | Value arrives as original type |
| Survives serialization | Yes (URL-safe) | No (transient, in-memory only) |

Use the string approach for deep links/URI-based navigation; use the object approach when you already have the data in memory and want to avoid a redundant lookup.
